  "abstract": "The OCC, the Board, the FDIC, and the OTS (collectively, the \"agencies\") are amending their Community Reinvestment Act (CRA) regulations to adjust the asset-size thresholds used to define \"small bank\" or \"small savings association\" and \"intermediate small bank\" or \"intermediate small savings association.\" As required by the CRA regulations, the adjustment to the threshold amount is based on the annual percentage change in the Consumer Price Index. The agencies are also correcting a paragraph hea",
